iNotes		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThis sound effect plugin is intended for audio devices with		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iall conditions met
below		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- A "speaker" rather than a "headphone" or an "earphone"		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Since the plugin will send bass through one channel and treble		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithrough the
other, it's meaningless for headphones		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Speakers for both channels placed together		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- If they are too far apart, you will feel that the bass and treble		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iare coming
from different places, hindering your experience.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- No dedicated bass unit		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- If it has one, the manufacturer likely had done everything this		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iplugin does,
to split bass to the dedicated unit		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- (Usually) inexpensive		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- If your speaker is pricey (like a JBL Charge 4), it usually has		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isuperior
bass effects anyway. Increasing bass further with this plugin		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imay damage
your hearing.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
