iInstallation & Usage		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThe sound effect plugin can be downloaded from my GitHub,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hhttps://github.com/xddxdd/ladspa	URL:https://github.com/xddxdd/ladspa	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i. Right now
(2020-02-18), there is only one plugin in the repo, the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifrequency splitter and
bass booster we're talking about, but I may add		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imore plugins if I want.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iIt can be installed just like any CMake project:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iSince it's a standard LADSPA plugin, it can be used by any music		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iplayer
supporting LADSPA, for example, Audacious:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
IAudacious Load LADSPA Plugin	/usr/uploads/202002/ladspa-audacity.png	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iHere `Split Frequency` stands for the split frequency for bass and		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
itreble. With
the settings in the picture, any sound lower than 100 Hz		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwill go through one
channel and be enhanced, while those higher than		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i100 Hz will go through the
other channel. `Bass Boost` is the factor		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iby which bass enhances. For example, 1
means no increase, and "5"		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imeans that the bass signal is multiplied by 5.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAs an alternative, you may also use PulseAudio to apply it to all		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isoftware. Add
the following instructions to the end of		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`/etc/pulse/default.pa`:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iHere 80 and 5 are for `Split Frequency` and `Bass Boost` individually.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThen
restart PulseAudio:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThen select Splitfreq as the default output device in the sound		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isettings.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAlgorithms		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThis sound effect plugin will randomly select a channel (corresponding		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ito a
speaker) as bass output and the other as treble output. This		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihappens at plugin
load time (usually when the player starts or		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iPulseAudio starts). It prevents
unbalanced speaker output if you've		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iused the plugin for too long and a speaker
begins to wear.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i> Although I don't think this has a high chance of happening, better		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ibe safe
than sorry.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThe plugin first takes the mean of input sound signal to mix the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isignal to mono
channel, since there's not much difference anyway on a		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iportable speaker. Then
the signal passes through a low-pass filter,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwith the threshold set to the value
of `Split Frequency`, to obtain		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithe bass signal. Treble signal is obtained by
subtracting the bass		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isignal from the input. The low-pass filter implementation
is copied		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifrom		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hLADSPA's Official Examples	URL:https://www.ladspa.org/ladspa_sdk/download.html	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThen the bass signal is multiplied by `Bass Boost` as enhancement, and		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ioutput to
the bass channel. The treble signal goes to the treble		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ichannel without any
enhancement.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iEffects		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iWith this plugin, the bass output on my speaker significantly		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iimproves. In
addition, with the separation of bass and treble, there		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iis no significant
distortion or volume change on the treble side.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iTherefore, my music experience
is greatly improved.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAbout parameter selection, on my Edifier M120, the best settings		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iare
`Split Frequency` set to 80 and `Bass Boost` set to 5. Since you		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i(almost)
definitely are using another speaker, you need to tune the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ibest parameters by
yourself.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
